    <fr:title text="Equivalence between NFA\varepsilons, NFAs, and DFAs › "><fr:link href="jms-017U.xml" title="Equivalence between NFA\varepsilons, NFAs, and DFAs" addr="jms-017U" type="local">Equivalence between <fr:link href="jms-017O.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions" addr="jms-017O" type="local">NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:link>s, <fr:link href="jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">NFA</fr:link>s, and <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link>s</fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>In <fr:link href="jms-00OD.xml" title="Soundness of the subset construction" addr="jms-00OD" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00OD" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="jms-00OE.xml" title="Completeness of the subset construction" addr="jms-00OE" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00OE" /></fr:link>, we have proved that <fr:link href="jms-017O.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions" addr="jms-017O" type="local">NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:link>s and <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link>s generate the same class of <fr:link href="jms-016M.xml" title="Formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">language</fr:link> as any <fr:link href="jms-017O.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions" addr="jms-017O" type="local">NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:link> can be converted into a <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link> recognising the same language. As any <fr:link href="jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">NFA</fr:link> is in particular an <fr:link href="jms-017O.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions" addr="jms-017O" type="local">NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:link>, we see that <fr:link href="jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">NFA</fr:link>s are equivalent to <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link>s in the same sense.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
