            <fr:title text="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions"><fr:link href="jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">Non-deterministic finite automaton</fr:link> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex>-transitions</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong><fr:link href="jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">non-deterministic finite automaton</fr:link> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex>-transitions</fr:strong></fr:em> or <fr:em><fr:strong>NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:strong></fr:em> for short is an <fr:link href="jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">NFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M = {\mathopen {}\left (Q,\Sigma ,\Delta ,s,F\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> together with an additional <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T\colon  Q\mathbin {\nrightarrow } Q]]></fr:tex> called the <fr:em><fr:strong><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex>-transition relation</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\mathrel {\xrightarrow {\varepsilon }}q']]></fr:tex> to mean that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\mathrel {T}q']]></fr:tex>. This notation is a little confusing! Note that this <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex> is not the same as the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ]]></fr:tex> denoting the empty <fr:link href="jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">string</fr:link>, and that therefore <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\mathrel {\xrightarrow {\varepsilon }}q']]></fr:tex> means something very different from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\mathrel {\vphantom {\xrightarrow {\epsilon }}\smash {\xrightarrow {\epsilon }}^*}
q']]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>11</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>14449</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-017L</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-017L.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Deterministic finite automaton">Deterministic finite automaton</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>deterministic finite automaton</fr:strong></fr:em> or <fr:em><fr:strong>DFA</fr:strong></fr:em> for short is an <fr:link href="jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">NFA</fr:link> for which the transition relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta \colon  Q\times  \Sigma \mathbin {\nrightarrow } Q]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">function</fr:link>, i.e. a <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">total</fr:link> and <fr:link href="jms-00K7.xml" title="Partial function" addr="jms-00K7" type="local">functional</fr:link> relation. This states, in other words, that to each state each state <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  Q]]></fr:tex> can transition along each symbol <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in \Sigma ]]></fr:tex> to one and only one state, which we conventionally write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta {\mathopen {}\left (q,a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Indeed, we will often write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M = (Q,\Sigma ,\delta ,s,F)]]></fr:tex> for a DFA. In this case, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q \mathrel {\xrightarrow {a}}q']]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta {\mathopen {}\left (q,a\right )\mathclose {}}=q']]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>11</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>6826</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-017M</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-017M.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Non-exclusive privatives in mathematical English">Non-exclusive privatives in mathematical English</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Aside</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>As an aside, it might feel strange to speak of “deterministic non-deterministic finite automata”. This is OK but can take some getting used to: mathematicians have discovered over the past several centuries that it is better for negations in terminology to mean “not necessarily” rather than “definitely not”; this is similar to the way that mathematicians often say “greater than” to mean “greater than or equal to”, reserving “strictly greater than” for the notion that excludes equality.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>11</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>14450</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-017H</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-017H.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Non-deterministic finite automaton">Non-deterministic finite automaton</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>non-deterministic finite automaton</fr:strong></fr:em> or <fr:em><fr:strong>NFA</fr:strong></fr:em> for short is defined to be a tuple <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M = {\mathopen {}\left (Q,\Sigma ,\Delta ,s,F\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> where:</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Q]]></fr:tex> is a finite set (of “states”).</fr:li>
 <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="jms-016H.xml" title="Alphabet" addr="jms-016H" type="local">alphabet</fr:link>, i.e. a finite set.</fr:li>
 <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta ]]></fr:tex> is a ternary relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta \colon  Q\times \Sigma \mathbin {\nrightarrow } Q]]></fr:tex> called the <fr:em>transition</fr:em> relation: we write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\xrightarrow {a}{q'}]]></fr:tex> to mean that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(q,a,q')\in \Delta ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
 <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> is an element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Q]]></fr:tex>, the “starting state”.</fr:li>
 <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Q]]></fr:tex>, the “accepting states”.</fr:li></fr:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>14451</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-016M</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-016M.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Formal language">Formal language</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>formal language</fr:strong></fr:em> over an <fr:link href="jms-016H.xml" title="Alphabet" addr="jms-016H" type="local">alphabet</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a <fr:em>subset</fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ^\star ]]></fr:tex>, i.e. a set of <fr:link href="jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">strings</fr:link> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>9</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>14452</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00OE</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00OE.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Completeness of the subset construction">Completeness of the <fr:link href="jms-017T.xml" title="Subset construction" addr="jms-017T" type="local">subset construction</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="jms-017O.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions" addr="jms-017O" type="local">NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:link>; then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}\subseteq \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>6841</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6098</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>unstable-6098.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="" />
                <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>We must show that any string <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> lies in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>6838</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6099</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>unstable-6099.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Empty string">Empty string</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Case</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=\epsilon ]]></fr:tex>, then we have assumed that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\xRightarrow {\epsilon }q]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in F_{M}]]></fr:tex>; therefore, by definition, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>. Thus we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\cap F_{M}]]></fr:tex> and so it follows by definition that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\in  F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>6840</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6100</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>unstable-6100.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Non-empty string">Non-empty string</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Case</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>Suppose that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=a_1\cdots  a_n]]></fr:tex>, and so we have transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\xRightarrow {a_1}q_1\xRightarrow {\cdots } q_{n-1}\xRightarrow {a_n}q_n]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_n\in F_{M}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                    <fr:p>We <fr:link href="jms-00KK.xml" title="Inductive definitions" addr="jms-00KK" type="local">inductively define</fr:link> a sequence of states <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_i]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
                    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \begin {aligned}
    S_0 &= s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\\
    S_{k+1} &= \delta _{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (S_k,a_{k+1}\right )\mathclose {}}
   \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>
                    <fr:p>Define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_0=s_{M}]]></fr:tex>. Then for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0\leq  i \leq  n]]></fr:tex>, we observe that we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_i\in  S_i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
                      <fr:frontmatter>
                        <fr:authors>
                          <fr:author>
                            <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                          </fr:author>
                        </fr:authors>
                        <fr:date>
                          <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                          <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                          <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                        </fr:date>
                        <fr:anchor>6839</fr:anchor>
                        <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6101</fr:addr>
                        <fr:route>unstable-6101.xml</fr:route>
                        <fr:title text="" />
                        <fr:taxon>Subproof</fr:taxon>
                      </fr:frontmatter>
                      <fr:mainmatter>
                        <fr:p>We proceed by induction on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex>. For <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i=0]]></fr:tex>, we need <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\in  s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>; but this holds by definition. Next, assuming <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_i\in  S_i]]></fr:tex> we must show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{i+1}\in  S_{i+1} = \delta _{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (S_i,a_{i+1}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Unfolding definitions, this follows from the transition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_i\xRightarrow {a_{i+1}} q_{i+1}]]></fr:tex> that we have assumed, as our inductive hypothesis ensures <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_i\in  S_i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                      </fr:mainmatter>
                    </fr:tree>
                    <fr:p>It follows from the above that we have transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0=s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\xrightarrow {a_1}S_1\xrightarrow {\cdots }S_{n-1}\xrightarrow {a_n}S_n]]></fr:tex>. Becuase we have shown <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_n\in  S_n]]></fr:tex> and we have assumed <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_n\in  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_n\in  F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>. Thus it follows that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> accepts <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="frankstajano.xml" title="Frank Stajano" addr="frankstajano" type="local">Frank Stajano</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="andrewpitts.xml" title="Andrew Pitts" addr="andrewpitts" type="local">Andrew Pitts</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>9</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>14453</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00OD</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00OD.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Soundness of the subset construction">Soundness of the <fr:link href="jms-017T.xml" title="Subset construction" addr="jms-017T" type="local">subset construction</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="jms-017O.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions" addr="jms-017O" type="local">NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:link>; then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}\subseteq  \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>6836</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6095</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>unstable-6095.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="" />
                <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>We must show that any <fr:link href="jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">string</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> lies in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>6547</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6096</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>unstable-6096.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Empty string">Empty string</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Case</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=\epsilon ]]></fr:tex>, then by definition we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\in F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> and so by definition, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>. By definition of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>, we therefore have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\mathrel {\xRightarrow {\epsilon }}q]]></fr:tex>; because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \in \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>6548</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6097</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>unstable-6097.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Non-empty string">Non-empty string</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Case</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>Suppose on the other hand that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=a_1\cdots  a_n]]></fr:tex>, and so we therefore have transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\mathrel {\xrightarrow {a_1}}S_1\mathrel {\xrightarrow {\ldots }}S_{n-1}\mathrel {\xrightarrow {a_n}}S_n]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_n\in  F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>, and so there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_n\in  S_n\cap  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>. Define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0 = s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                    <fr:p>By definition of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, from the transition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_{n-1}\mathrel {\xrightarrow {a_n}}S_n]]></fr:tex> we may find some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{n-1}\in  S_{n-1}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{n-1}\mathrel {\xRightarrow {a_n}}q_n]]></fr:tex>. Iterating this process, we may find states <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_i\in  S_{i}]]></fr:tex> such that we have a sequence of transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{i-1}\mathrel {\xRightarrow {a_i}}q_i]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>; thus we have a sequence of transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_0\mathrel {\xRightarrow {u}}q_n]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_0\in  S_0=s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\mathrel {\xRightarrow {\epsilon }}q_0]]></fr:tex> and thus <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\mathrel {\xRightarrow {\epsilon }}q_0\mathrel {\xRightarrow {u}}q_n]]></fr:tex> and therefore <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\mathrel {\xRightarrow {u}} q_n]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_n\in  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>, we are done.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
